# Walkthrough - Project RAKSHA-NETRA Simulator

We have successfully built and verified the software application for **Project RAKSHA-NETRA** 

This application functions as a high-fidelity interactive simulation and an interactive pitch deck for hackathon judges, presenting the technical architecture, operational user interfaces, and business model in a cohesive, premium web dashboard.


## 📁 Files Created

1. **[index.html](file:///C:/Users/nagas/.gemini/antigravity-ide/scratch/raksha-netra/index.html)**: Defines the structural grid of the application, splitting it into a simulated Physical Track simulator, the Station Master command console, the Loco Pilot smartphone app, and a modal containing the Pitch Deck slides.
2. **[style.css](file:///C:/Users/nagas/.gemini/antigravity-ide/scratch/raksha-netra/style.css)**: Implements the visual styling including a slate dark mode, futuristic glowing nodes, glassmorphic panels, keyframe flashing alarms, and a bezel smartphone mockup frame.
3. **[app.js](file:///C:/Users/nagas/.gemini/antigravity-ide/scratch/raksha-netra/app.js)**: Implements the logic loops (10Hz sampling check), train speed/braking physics, multi-sensor voting logic, LoRa mesh hops, real-time vibration scrolling canvas graph, dynamic SVG vision drawings, and synthetic audio siren.
4. **[server.ps1](file:///C:/Users/nagas/.gemini/antigravity-ide/scratch/raksha-netra/server.ps1)**: A native, lightweight PowerShell web server utilizing built-in .NET classes (`HttpListener`) to serve files locally on port `8888` without any external package dependencies.

